25/03/2004
LISBON, Portugal -- British Prime Minister Tony Blair said Wednesday (24 March) that the EU should admit Turkey to underscore its commitment to the creation of a tolerant and diverse Europe. 
"Let us show by our willingness to bring Turkey, a proud Muslim nation, into the EU on the same and equal terms as all others, that Europe is committed . 
to a Europe of diverse races, cultures and religions," he said.
In other news, Turkish State Minister Mehmet Aydin warned on Wednesday that if the EU fails to set a date to begin accession negotiations at its December summit, it would harm relations with Turkey, cultivated over decades. 
(AFP, Anadolu Agency - 24/03/04)
